add_arenas

Clair Chaigne

17 mai 2021

1. INSTRUCTIONS

1.1 EXPLANATION

After tracking simultaneously 96 arenas, the files given by the Noldus does not contain Arena 1, Arena 2, ..., Arena 96 for the Arena column but instead contain 1, 2, ... 96.

For the wakefish program to work, it uses Arena as a keyword to detect the Arena column.

You can use the add_arenas R script to add Arena from files in the without folder to the with folder.

1.2 STEPS

  1. empty the without folder
  2. put the files to modify in the `without' folder
  3. launch add_arenas.R (either launch each line with Ctrl+Enter or Ctrl+Alt+R to run all the lines)
  4. open each file from the 'with' folder and manually copy the Arena column in each corresponding file in the 'without' folder. Use the files in the 'without' folder to run the wakefish program.

1.3 TO CHECK IF THERE ARE ANY ISSUES

  1. be sure you have the correct libraries installed in R studio : readxl and writexl (if they are not installed, an error message "aucun package nomme 'nomdelalibrairie' n'est trouve" should appear). To install the library run this command : install.packages("nomdelalibrarie")
  2. be sure that number n defining the column arena is correct (3 for third column)
  3. be sure that the number m for number of arenas is correct (96 for 96 arenas)

2. EXAMPLE

for this example I used the Statistics-LDlak3F1 file (you can find it in Y:\ELISE DATA_17Gb a trier\EXCELL+stats\excell\zebrafish locomotor activity\lakritz\LD\LDlak3\1.statsLDlak3)

  • this first line allows to clean the R studio environment (remove functions, variables, data frames etc... to start with a clean workplace)
rm(list=ls())

2.0 LIBRARIES

  • this loads the required libraries
library(readxl)
library(writexl)
## Warning: package 'writexl' was built under R version 4.0.5

if you get an error message such as Error in library(readxl) : aucun package nomme 'readxl' n'est trouve, run this line : install.packages("readxl")and then try to load the libraries again. ----

  • this defines the numbers corresponding to the arena column and number of arenas :

check that these numbers are correct

n <- 3  # define the column arena
m <- 96  # number of arenas

2.1 DEFINE FOLDERS

  • this defines the folder where the original files are (without) and the output files will be (with)
setwd("Y://Clair//for_Elise//add_arenas//without")  # input files
dossier_sortie <- "Y://Clair//for_Elise//add_arenas//with"  # output files

2.2 LOAD FILES

  • this retrieves the names of all the files present in this folder

check here if all your files are correctly listed

nom_fichiers <- list.files()
nom_fichiers
## [1] "Statistics-LDlak3F1.xlsx"
  • this loads the files in a list and name them correctly
fichiers <- list()
for (i in 1:length(nom_fichiers))
{
  fichiers[[i]] <- read_excel(nom_fichiers[i], col_names = FALSE)
}
## New names:
## * `` -> ...1
## * `` -> ...2
## * `` -> ...3
## * `` -> ...4
## * `` -> ...5
## * ...
names(fichiers) <- sub('\\.xlsx$', '', nom_fichiers)

2.3 ADD ARENAS

  • for each file in the list, this adds Arena in the nth column for m arenas
for (i in 1:length(nom_fichiers))
{
  j <- 1
  for(j in 1:m)
  {
    fichiers[[i]][, n][fichiers[[i]][, n]==j] <- paste("Arena", j, sep = " ")
  }
}

2.4 EXPORT FILES

  • this exports each file from the list in the 'with' folder and add -arena to their name
nom_fichiers <- sub('\\.xlsx$', '', nom_fichiers)
for (i in 1:length(nom_fichiers))
{
  write_xlsx(fichiers[[i]], path = paste(dossier_sortie, "//",nom_fichiers[i], "-arena.xlsx", sep = ""), col_names = FALSE)
}

2.5 MANUALLY MODIFY THE WITHOUT FILES

  • open the files from the withoutfolder and manually paste the arena column from the corresponding file from the withfolder

  • use the manually modified files from the without folder for wakefish
